      <relatedmaterial>
        <head>Related Collections</head>
        <p>The Michigan Veteran Feminists Oral Histories Project contains an interview of Federbush. Housed in the Bentley Historical Library, the collection contains interviews of women who were influential in Michigan's feminist movement.</p>
        <p>Harvard's Arthur and Elizabeth Schlesinger Library on the History of Women in America have records of the Women's Equity Action League. This collection contains records of the SPRINT project and some folders of correspondence by Federbush. Below is a link to the finding aid:</p>
        <p>http://oasis.lib.harvard.edu/oasis/deliver/~sch00301</p>
      </relatedmaterial>
